title: Photo: Justin Bieber shows off new tattoo
text:
By Andrea Park CBS News October 7, 2015, 5:09 PM Justin Bieber shows off new tattoo 
Justin Bieber attends the 2015 MTV Video Music Awards at Microsoft Theater on August 30, 2015 in Los Angeles. Jason Merritt/Getty Images More + 
Justin Bieber has a purpose, or a tattoo that says "Purpose," at least. 
The pop star showed off fresh ink on his abs could be a more abstract take on the word, but it also may refer to the singer's latest album, also called "Purpose." 
The "What Do You Mean" singer posted the picture on Instagram with the caption: "#purpose." 
Bieber already has plenty of tattoos. He got his first tattoo when he was only 16, and hasn't looked back. As of last year, the pop star had more than 30 tattoos from notable artists like Bang Bang and Seunghyun Jo.
